userStories.notes:
Starlight's search uses Pagefind. The trigger button is inside a <starlight-search> custom element. Target via CSS in global.css:
starlight-search button { border: 2px solid var(--border); border-radius: 0; box-shadow: var(--shadow-sm); transition: all 0.2s; }
starlight-search button:hover { box-shadow: none; transform: translateY(1px); }
For the search modal: dialog[open] { border: 2px solid var(--border); border-radius: 0; box-shadow: var(--shadow-lg); }
Search input: .pagefind-ui__search-input { border: 2px solid var(--border) !important; border-radius: 0 !important; box-shadow: var(--shadow-md); }
Use !important sparingly -- only where Pagefind's inline styles override.

Starlight's mobile menu button is a <starlight-menu-button> custom element containing a <button>. Target in global.css:
starlight-menu-button button { border: 2px solid var(--border); border-radius: 0; box-shadow: var(--shadow-sm); background: var(--background); transition: all 0.2s; }
starlight-menu-button button:hover { box-shadow: none; transform: translateY(1px); }

Target in global.css:
.sidebar-content .top-level > li > details > summary, .sidebar-content .top-level > li > span { font-family: var(--font-head); font-size: 0.9rem; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border); padding-bottom: 0.5rem; margin-bottom: 0.25rem; }
Sidebar links: nav.sidebar a { transition: color 0.2s; } nav.sidebar a:hover { color: var(--primary); }
Active link (update existing rule): nav.sidebar a[aria-current='page'] { border-left: 2px solid var(--primary); background-color: color-mix(in srgb, var(--accent) 20%, transparent); padding-left: 0.75rem; }
Sidebar right border on desktop: @media (min-width: 72rem) { .sidebar-pane { border-right: 2px solid var(--border); } }
Note: Starlight's sidebar HTML structure uses .sidebar-content with nested <ul> and <details> for collapsible groups. Inspect the built HTML to get exact selectors.

Starlight renders social links as <a> elements inside .social-icons in the header. Target:
.social-icons a { border: 2px solid var(--border); border-radius: 0; box-shadow: var(--shadow-sm); padding: 0.375rem; background: var(--background); transition: all 0.2s; }
.social-icons a:hover { box-shadow: none; transform: translateY(1px); background: var(--muted); }

Add to global.css body rule: background: var(--background); color: var(--foreground); (currently only has font-family).

Add RetroUI scrollbar styles (from ~/Downloads/RetroUI-main/app/global.css lines 371-494):
html { scrollbar-width: auto; scrollbar-color: var(--muted) var(--foreground); }
.sidebar-scroll { scrollbar-width: thin; scrollbar-color: transparent transparent; transition: scrollbar-color 0.3s ease; }
.sidebar-scroll:hover { scrollbar-color: var(--color-primary) transparent; }
.sidebar-scroll::-webkit-scrollbar { width: 2px; height: 2px; }
.sidebar-scroll::-webkit-scrollbar-track { background: transparent; }
.sidebar-scroll::-webkit-scrollbar-thumb { background: transparent; border-radius: 2px; }

